# Float4 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: float4)')
!tx 'insert (3.5e39) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `FLOAT4`
>   1 │ insert (3.5e39) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `3.5e39` does not fit into `FLOAT4` (range: -3.4e38 to +3.4e38)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `FLOAT4`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
